{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review and reform education system to support neurodivergent children in schools",
        "additional_details": "Every child deserves to learn \u2014 not just to cope. Review and reform schools, respect differences, and recognise neurodiversity. Inclusion isn\u2019t optional \u2014 it\u2019s every child\u2019s right. Support neurodivergent children, because change starts in our classrooms. Different minds have the same right to thrive. Education should fit the child, not force the child to fit. Build schools that embrace every mind.",
        "background": "I want the government to review and reform mainstream education so neurodivergent children are understood, supported, and included \u2014 with trained teachers, sensory-friendly classrooms, proper funding, and accountability under the Equality and Disability Acts.",
